    <string name="boundary_text_plain">After you upload a file, Verum Omnis copies it into the app, locks the intake details, and runs the forensic engine on this device. The system reads OCR text, page images, signatures, overlays, dates, contradictions, money trails, and behaviour patterns so the report can show what happened, who appears to be involved, and which pages support each point.</string>
    <string name="hero_headline">Upload evidence here first.</string>
    <string name="hero_summary">Pick the file at the top. The video and the full platform detail sit underneath.</string>
    <string name="section_how_it_works">What happens after upload</string>
    <string name="section_architecture">Privacy, stateless operation, and trust</string>
    <string name="section_sealing">Pricing, access, and retention</string>
    <string name="section_gemma">Gemma after the forensic run</string>
    <string name="section_case_files">Case files, scan folders, and sealing</string>
    <string name="section_case_files_body">Create dated scan folders, merge multiple scans into one case file, then seal the narrative as the official case record.</string>
    <string name="constitution_status_plain">Verum Omnis is stateless by design. Each run starts from the evidence you upload now, not hidden conversation memory and not a live internet session. The engine works locally, keeps the originals under your control, and only writes vault artifacts or exports when you choose to do that.</string>
    <string name="business_model_plain" formatted="false">Private citizens and law enforcement use Verum Omnis free. Commercial and institutional matters get a 30-day review window after upload before paid release rules apply. For business legal matters, pricing is set at 20% of the ordinary lawyer cost in the users area. For private tax-return work, pricing is 50% of the lowest comparable local accountant cost after the supervised beta window. Sealed files remain tied to the exact evidence set that produced them, so later changes break the seal.</string>
    <string name="front_page_status_format">Court validation: %1$s&#10;&#10;Active matters currently tracked inside this build: %2$s.</string>
    <string name="gemma_front_page_plain">Gemma works from the sealed forensic case package, not from raw evidence and not from internet guesswork. She is there to explain findings in plain English, help users understand likely next steps, and keep the legal guidance tied to the vault on this device.</string>
    <string name="video_intro_title">Watch the walkthrough</string>
    <string name="video_intro_body">The video sits here on purpose. Watch it after the upload controls if you want the wider explanation of the platform, the vault, and the constitutional model. It does not autoplay.</string>
